properties.Des_Intent: A variety of uses allowed, including residential, commercial, and light industrial with the general goal of preserving the residential character of surrounding neighborhoods.
properties.Des_App: Portions of Townsite, Mud Bay Road, and areas currently zoned as “General Use” that are not primarily residential.

properties.Des_Intent: Areas devoted to light and heavy industrial uses.
properties.Des_App: Landfill, Airport, Spruce Grove Road, Well Field Road, Lutak Dock, and portions of Haines Hwy at 4-mile.
properties.Des_Use: Light: Processing & Manufacturing; Heavy: Gravel pits, airports, Freight Docks

properties.Des_Intent: Areas to remain in a natural state due to conservation value or hazard potential, not managed by State or Federal governments.
properties.Des_App: Greenways, portions of Sawmill Watershed, Lily Lake

properties.Des_Intent: State and federal lands with multiple uses, to remain in public ownership, including flood protection, habitat value, traditional use, recreation, tourism, timber extraction, and mining. State and federal land agencies to set land use priorities.
properties.Des_App: Majority of the borough not within residential areas (state parks, Haines State Forest, Tongass National Forest, Bureau of Land Management recreation management areas).
properties.Des_Use: Uses designated by State and Federal governments.

properties.Des_Intent: Predominantly residential areas that do not have access to public water utilities. Mostly low density, and larger lot sizes (1 acre+). Includes some commercial uses.
properties.Des_App: Neighborhoods within the Upper Chilkat Valley, Mud Bay, Excursion Inlet, Lutak, and some areas within the Townsite.
properties.Des_Use: Single residential, agriculture enterprises, cottage industries.

properties.Des_Intent: Waterfront dependent uses that combine light industrial, recreation, and commercial uses, balancing working waterfronts with community spaces.
properties.Des_App: Portage Cove, Letnikof Cove, and Excursion Inlet.
properties.Des_Use: Boat harbors, docks, retail, parks, canneries.

properties.Des_Intent: Predominately residential areas with compatible public and commercial uses; areas for infill and densification, including neighborhoods that currently have access to public water utilities, typically less than one acre.
properties.Des_App: Neighborhoods within the Townsite Service Area with access to public utilities.
properties.Des_Use: Single and multi-residential, pocket parks, corner stores.

properties.Des_Intent: Areas developed for parks, campgrounds, cemeteries, or indoor recreation, not managed by State or Federal governments.
properties.Des_App: Parks, Jones Point Cemetery, Haines School.

properties.Des_Intent: Areas for continuing infill and densification, with a focus on mixed use development, walkability, redevelopment, and policies for compatibility between differing uses. This is the primary downtown business district in Haines.
properties.Des_App: Sixth Avenue to Portage Cove (West to East) and Union Street to Fort Seward (North to South).
properties.Des_Use: Mixed-use retail, government buildings, gas service stations.

properties.Des_Intent: Areas for commercial and higher density residential uses; compact, walkable, and diverse.
properties.Des_App: Portions of Townsite and Haines Highway.

properties.Des_Intent: Key rivers and riverfront areas. Includes suggested setbacks to protect riparian habitat (actual regulations will vary by location).
properties.Des_App: Chilkat, Chilkoot, Ferebee, and Katzehin river systems.
properties.Des_Use: Uses designated by State and Federal governments.
